description:
A delicious cluster of blueberries.
Recovers 15% life on pickup!
name: Blueberries

description:
A scrumptious bunch of grapes.
Recovers 15% magi on pickup!
name: Blackberries

description:
An energizing pair of cherries.
Recovers 15 tech on pickup!
name: Cherries

description:
Restores life to max and revives all dead members.
Made from the rarest of medicinal ingredients.
name: Serum

description: Restores magi to max.
name: Ether

description: Purges all negative status ailments.
name: Remedy

description:
A small heartfruit, though ambrosial, is barely ripe.
Heals 15% HP/MP and restores from dead- for the whole party!
name: Tiny Heartfruit

description:
A legendary ambrosial fruit, grown in the Gardens of Eden.
Heals all HP/MP and restores from dead- for the whole party!
name: Heartfruit

description:
Unrefined rouge matter.
You'll need to refine it through alchemy if you want to use it.
name: Raw Rouge Matter

description:
Unrefined bleu matter.
You'll need to refine it through alchemy if you want to use it.
name: Raw Bleu Matter

description:
Unrefined verte matter.
You'll need to refine it through alchemy if you want to use it.
name: Raw Verte Matter

description:
Unrefined jaune matter.
You'll need to refine it through alchemy if you want to use it.
name: Raw Jaune Matter

description:
Unrefined blanche matter.
You'll need to refine it through alchemy if you want to use it.
name: Raw Blanche Matter

description:
Unrefined noire matter.
You'll need to refine it through alchemy if you want to use it.
name: Raw Noire Matter

description:
Refined rouge matter, radiating with the heat element.
Use in crafting of any type to add a touch of heat to things.
name: Rouge Essence

description:
Refined bleu matter, radiating with the liquid element.
Use in crafting of any type to add a splash of liquidity to things.
name: Bleu Essence

description:
Refined verte matter, radiating with the air element.
Use in crafting of any type to improve the flow of things.
name: Verte Essence

description:
Refined jaune matter, radiating with the ground element.
Use in crafting of any type to add some grit to things.
name: Jaune Essence

description:
Refined blanche matter, radiating with the energy element.
Use in crafting of any type to add a sense of absolute purity to things.
name: Blanche Essence

description:
Refined noire matter, radiating with the void element.
Use in crafting of any type to add that missing something to things.
name: Noire Essence

description:
Ultra-concentrated and refined rouge essence.
A few drops of this and anything you're crafting will radiate intense heat.
name: Pure Rouge

description:
Ultra-concentrated and refined bleu essence.
A few drops of this and anything you're crafting will become aqueous.
name: Pure Bleu

description:
Ultra-concentrated and refined verte essence.
A few drops of this and anything you're crafting will be light as a feather.
name: Pure Verte

description:
Ultra-concentrated and refined jaune essence.
A few drops of this and anything you're crafting will be solid as rock.
name: Pure Jaune

description:
Ultra-concentrated and refined blanche essence.
A few drops of this and anything you're crafting will become blessed.
name: Pure Blanche

description:
Ultra-concentrated and refined noire essence.
A few drops of this and anything you're crafting will become cursed.
name: Pure Noire

description:
Raw iron ore.
It can be used as-is, but removing impurities would improve the quality.
name: Iron Ore

description:
Forge-ready iron.
This is the most basic of basic, can be used to craft many things.
name: Iron Ingot

description:
Raw silver ore.
It can be used as-is, but removing impurities would improve the quality.
name: Silver Ore

description:
Forge-ready silver.
Silver gear has a natural effectiveness versus undead creatures.
name: Silver Ingot

description:
Raw bleu ore.
It can be used as-is, but removing impurities would improve the quality.
name: Bleu Ore

description:
Forge-ready bleu metal.
Bleu is an alchemized metal that is known for being sturdy.
name: Bleu Ingot

description:
Raw sandwraith ore.
It can be used as-is, but removing impurities would improve the quality.
name: Sandwraith Ore

description:
Forge-ready sandwraith metal.
Weapons forged from sandwraith metal are extremely sharp and lightweight.
name: Sandwraith Ingot

description:
Raw magmite ore.
It can be used as-is, but removing impurities would improve the quality.
name: Magmite Ore

description:
Forge-ready magmite.
Magmite is an alchemized metal that boasts incredible magical energy.
name: Magmite Ingot

description:
Raw deep ore.
It can be used as-is, but removing impurities would improve the quality.
name: Deep Ore

description:
Forge-ready deep metal.
Deep metals are renowned worldwide for their effectiveness against constructs.
name: Deep Ingot

description:
Raw might ore.
It can be used as-is, but removing impurities would improve the quality.
name: Might Ore

description:
Forge-ready might metal.
Might metal gear tends to amplify attributes of the wearer.
name: Might Ingot

description:
Raw ultanium ore.
It can be used as-is, but removing impurities would improve the quality.
name: Ultanium Ore

description:
Forge-ready ultanium. The rarity alone makes this ingot worth millions,
in addition to the insane durability and sharpness. Literally unparalleled.
name: Ultanium Ingot

description:
A large blob of green gelatinous shit you scooped up from a slime.
Eating it raw is probably a bad idea.
name: Big Gelatin

description:
It looks like a mess of what was once a Big Gelatin.
Maybe it still can be used for something?
name: Splattered Jelly

description:
The broken skull of some...thing. It is tough to say what it
originally was, given there are no other parts attached.
name: Broken Skull

description:
It almost just looks like a pure white cloth sheet.
It is a bit torn, though.
name: Ghostly Veil

description:
It is unclear what this is, other than an odorless white powder.
Maybe ground bones? Temperature-defying snow? Who knows.
name: Odorless Powder

description:
Cheese is just moldy, cultured milk... but this cheese is VERY old.
Use caution if you plan on eating it straight or cooking with it!
name: Really Old Cheese

description:
The stinger of a bee.
It looks to be cracked somehow. The bee probably was in a lot of pain.
name: Cracked Stinger

description:
A wing of some kind of avian creature.
It is clearly damaged- definitely not suitable for flight.
name: Damaged Wing

description:
A large glob of honey, from a needler of some sort.
This can be used to add sweetness to any dish!
name: Honey Blob

description:
A root from a very durable plant of some kind.
Can be used in all facets of crafting for various purposes.
name: Tough Root

description:
A part of the family of nightshades.
Known specifically for it's deadly toxic qualities.
name: Wolfsbane

description:
One of the 8 vines a wolftrap possesses. The plant has a ton of great
nutritional benefits, but is best known for restoring mental accuity.
name: Wolftrap Vine

description:
A single talon from the claw of a beast.
The rest of the talons are missing.
name: Busted Claw

description:
The fur from a beast of some kind.
It appears to be ripped up and disheveled.
name: Ripped Fur

description:
A regular slab of meat off the flank of a bearcat.
When cooked, it tastes a bit like beef. Uncooked, and it tastes like ass.
name: Bearcat Flank

description:
It is water. A small bottle of it. Plain old water, nothing fancy.
You can probably drink it, but by itself, the effects would be minimal.
name: Water

description:
The scale off of a kappa. Who knew they had scales?
It is tough to know what this'd be used for.
name: Kappa Scale

description:
A cod from a body of freshwater. It looks like it is surprisingly fresh 
despite where you got it. Probably should cook it before eating, though.
name: Freshwater Cod

description:
A bundle of various aromatics that add wonderful smells to
any recipe.
name: Aromatic Herbs

description:
Regular old butter. Can be used for all sorts of things in
cooking and baking.
name: Butter

description:
Rice grains that have been milled and polished to perfection.
Cook with water to make the fluffiest of rice!
name: Rice

description:
It is difficult to say what animal this milk is from, but it
doesn't offend the senses, so it isn't that important, is it?
name: Milk

description:
The standard of fruit. Use it to add a touch of acidity to
your dish, or cook it to make the finest sauce in the land.
name: Tomato

description:
It is probably just salt, but calling it that would make
it difficult to flex for other types of dishes that need seasoning.
name: Seasoning

description:
The size of the egg mean it probably didn't come from
a chicken...
name: Egg

description: A nice olive-like oil to saute your favorite foods in.
name: Cooking Oil

description:
Your basic yellow onion. Slightly sweet, but has a delicate
aroma that wafts deep into your happy little nostrils.
name: Onion

description:
Carrots are well-known for their rabbit consumers, but rabbits
if you added this to a stew, it would definitely add earthiness!
name: Carrot

description:
The most versatile of roots, the potato can be used for
so many things its an absolute atrocity you don't have 999 of them.
name: Potato

description:
An old hand-me-down utensil. Can be used to boil and stew a variety
of different soup-like dishes!
name: Soup Pot

description:
A fine cooking utensil. Some dishes require the ability to
stir the contents without your bare hands to produce sanitary results.
name: Spoon

description:
An old hand-me-down utensil. Can be used to saute, fry, or sear
a variety of different ingredients!
name: Frying Pan

description:
A fine cooking utensil. Some dishes require the finesse of
a turner like this to safely flip to the other side for even cooking.
name: Spatula

description:
A strange-looking pudding that is a delicacy in Erocy.
Seem to smell like oranges... but at least it heals life, magi, AND tech!
name: Erocian Pudding

description:
A classic Erocian dish, according to The Comfy Bear's innkeeper.
It is a strange honey-based soup with floating bits of vine in it.
name: Yellow Soup

description:
A classic Erocian dish, according to The Comfy Bear's innkeeper.
It seems simple enough: seasoned bearcat flank that has been grilled.
name: Grilled Bearcat

description:
A classic Erocian dish, according to The Comfy Bear's innkeeper.
A beautiful cod that has been panseared in butter.
name: Pan-seared Cod

description:
A classic Erocian dish, according to The Comfy Bear's innkeeper.
Some eggs that were cooked in that really old cheese you found.
name: Fried Cheesy Eggs

description:
A fine smithing tool. Some blueprints require a hammer
to do blacksmith things.
name: Smithing Hammer

description:
A fine smithing tool. Some blueprints call for steps that include
sticking your hands in the flames. These protect you from that.
name: Smithing Mitts

description:
A small pile of smelling salts that will snap the whole party back from the dead.
Also heals some Life (15% + 150).
name: Smelling Salts

description: After you obliterated this creature, this is all that was left.
name: Chipped Fang

description:
A surprisingly intact wing from a bat. Not sure what bat, but it is
definitely from some kind of bat.
name: Bat Wing

description:
This appears to be the skull from the floaty flaming skull monster.
However, the flames have gone out, and now the skull looks much more shrunken than before.
name: Collapsed Skull

description:
It looks like some extra meaty ribs off a cow... but there aren't any
cows on this planet, so where did it come from?
name: Raw Ribs

description:
Looks like it was a pickaxe that did things once, but now after
the bullheaded fucker beat you with it a few times, it is broken.
name: Broken Pickaxe

description:
No matter how much you look straight into this eye, it never looks like
it is looking back at you.
name: Blank Eye

description:
The wraith is a terrifying undead entity, but damn are it's robes silky smooth.
With this thread, you can also have a sexy sleek undead garb!
name: Undead Thread

description:
All fungus is edible for the most part, including this fungus! However...
Some still can wreak havoc on your insides if you're unlucky. Eat with caution!
name: Growing Fungus

description:
This is often identified as a delicacy due to the elusiveness of the Jelli.
However, there aren't many recipes that utilize it.
name: Jelli Jelly

description:
The petals from a flower found in the Forest of Dreams.
It is probably used in JAFTING, but you can't tell based on the petals alone.
name: Dream Petals

description:
A tiny acorn that the Dryad was holding onto.
Said to contain the memories of this Dryad and it's previous generations.
name: Dryad's Acorn

description:
What are you, some kind of monster? Why did you rip these teeth clean out of
the beasts face? You are rude and a jerk. You should put them back.
name: Beast Fangs

description:
This is pretty gross to actually carry around, much less carry multiple around.
It is bloody, wet, squishy, and is starting to smell bad.
name: Animal Heart

description:
An uncommon Erocian dish, according to nature lover.
A roll made from fried potatoes as the container and beef with cheese as the filling.
name: Potato Beef Cake

description:
An uncommon Erocian dish, according to nature lover.
Beautifully charred rib meat that has been seasoned to perfection. Would even revive the dead.
name: Charred Beef Ribs

description:
This is an amazing nut-based pie, derived from none other than the Dryad's
Acorns. The memories of the Dryad are so delicious that they purge all poisons.
name: Acorn Pie

description:
An uncommon Erocian dish, according to nature lover.
A strangely jiggly pilaf that smells much better than it looks.
name: Jelli Pilaf

description:
An uncommon Erocian dish, according to nature lover.
A spread of carrots that have been glazed in honey before roasting.
name: Honeyroasted Carrots

description:
An uncommon Erocian dish, according to nature lover.
A tiny bowl of bisque crafted from a variety of wild fungus.
name: Mushroom Bisque

description:
A rare Erocian dish, according to nature lover.
A sumptuous stew with a never-before-seen amount of umami delivering 💯%.
name: Tasty Stew

description:
A common survival tool. You can't use this for fighting with, but
it would do well for precision-cutting fabric and the like while JAFTING.
name: Scissors

description:
A common survival tool. When things are tiny and/or hard to see,
use this and... well, you'll be able to see the tiny/hard-to-see things.
name: Magnifying Glass

description:
A rare survival tool. Some say the pen is mightier than the sword,
but have you ever tried to literally combat a swordsman with a pen? At least it writes.
name: Fountain Pen

description:
Not everything should rest directly in your infinite bag of holding. For those
cases, you should consider putting them in a container such as this.
name: Container

description:
Play the ukelele vigorously and destroy things with the power of sound.
The ukelele can destroy certain stone spires.
name: Ukelele

description:
An explosive that detonates after a few seconds.
Bombs can destroy walls that are already cracked.
name: Time Bomb

description:
A magical wand with a flame on the tip that never goes out.
The flame isn't hot or even dangerous to humanoids, but it lights special torches just right!
name: Red Wand

description:
Unlocks "Enchanter's Guile".
Earned from story progression.
name: Enchanter's Guile

description:
Unlocks "Fighter's Spirit".
Earned from story progression.
name: Fighter's Spirit

description:
Unlocks "Ghostly Presence".
Drops from ghosties in the Erocian Lair.
name: Ghostly Presence

description:
Unlocks "Erocian Strong Style".
Drops from erocian slimes in the Erocian Lair.
name: Erocian Strong Style

description:
Unlocks "Sting like a Bee".
Drops from various bees across the land.
name: Sting like a Bee

name: Tentacular Touch

description:

description:

description:

Drops from the Will'o'wisps in the Raevula Mines.
name: Flame's Caress

description:
Unlocks "Bullheaded".
Drops from various minotaurs across the land.
name: Bullheaded

description:
Unlocks "Otherworldly Dark".
Drops from various wraiths across the land.
name: Otherworldly Dark

description:

Drops from various sprouts across the land.
name: Pissed Off Sprout

description:

Drops from various jelli monsters across the land.
name: Flowing Fluids

description:
Unlocks "Fae's Scorn".
Drops from various faeries across the land.
name: Scorn of Fae

description:
Unlocks "Thief's Code".
Drops from the bandits in the Forest of Dreams.
name: Thief's Code

description:
Unlocks "Glutton's Dogma".
Drops from the werewolves in the Forest of Dreams.
name: Glutton's Dogma

description:
Unlocks "Burrow Burr".
Drops from the crawlers in the Forlorn Basin.
name: Burrow Burr

description:
Unlocks "Soak 'n' Spray".
Drops from the goobats in the Forlorn Basin.
name: Soak 'n' Spray

description:
Unlocks "Stone's Secret".
Drops from the stonefurs in the Forlorn Basin.
name: Stone's Secret

description:
Unlocks "Goo Tango".
Drops from the Slime in the Forlorn Basin.
name: Goo Tango

description:
Unlocks "Bloody Embrace".
Drops from various tentacles across the land.
name: Bloody Embrace

description:
Unlocks "Ironfist of Iron".
Drops from various minotaurs across the land.
name: Ironfist of Iron

description:
Unlocks "Boney Situation".
Drops from the skeletors in the outer cliffs.
name: Boney Situation

description:
Unlocks "Spinal Control".
Drops from the skeledoggos in the outer cliffs.
name: Spinal Control

description:
Unlocks "Princely Flourish".
Drops from the prince cobra in the outer cliffs.
name: Princely Flourish

description:
Unlocks "Pressure Points".
Drops from the penetrators in the meandering way.
name: Pressure Points
